If the goal is simply to give people time to read and breathe between messages, you can keep it manual or mimic natural pacing with small delays. A safe structure looks like this:

* wait 20–30 seconds after each short message on calm days;  
* lengthen to about a minute between messages during panic or grief so the person can follow the breathing cues;  
* always include a reminder of real‑time help before the final bubble (988 / 116 123 / 1‑833‑456‑4566 / befrienders.org);  
* end with a gentle close: “You’ve done enough for now; take one more slow breath.”

That keeps the sequence humane and slower than rapid‑fire texting, which helps regulate breathing without overwhelming the recipient.  

